<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: PerK</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-28 17:39:32</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, here's the scoop.  The cloak *should* not be as expensive<BR>
as it is all things considered.  Not that I am complaining.<BR>
It drops off the Goblin Alchemist in Permafrost.  He is a <BR>
level ~25 shaman type mob.  He spawns in a room with one<BR>
other lower ~22 gob.  Its a 20 minute spawn, and it seems<BR>
to average around 4-5 placeholders (~25 some healers you have<BR>
to watch out for) per Alch.  In my expereince (four cloaks)<BR>
he drops a cloak ever 6-8 spawns, so it can be a while before<BR>
you get one.  I seem to average about six hours sitting<BR>
at the spawn reading a book.  All in all, a level 29 that<BR>
can get back to the room (ie invis) should have no problem.<BR>
Its just a boring as heck camp.  The main reason its so<BR>
rare is that Perma rarely has anyone in it.  It is almost<BR>
always fully spawned back to the Alch.  BTW, make sure you<BR>
split up the spawns and control the runners.  If a healer<BR>
pops while another goby is beating on you, its gate or die<BR>
at 29.  A runner will bring around 20 gobs back with him,<BR>
so if one gets out, just gate.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Quale</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-03 17:25:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I would consider myself very lucky if 6 hours was enough to get<BR>
the cloak. I camped it recently and it took 4 hours just to see<BR>
the alchemist spawn the first time. It finally dropped after 10<BR>
straight hours. I talked to someone who had camped it for 18 hours<BR>
without it dropping.<BR>
Also becareful about relying completely on invis to sneak in<BR>
there. Several goblin types that spawn in the tunnel are casters<BR>
and they will see through your invis when you least expect it.<BR>
It got me killed once and forced me to gate 3-4 times.<BR>
I don't think the cloak is pricey at all after having done the<BR>
camp. It is dreary and dangerous and considering the availability<BR>
of non plane wisdom cloaks, I'd say it's worth more than the average<BR>
price on Max EQ.<BR>
The person that camped and got the drop before me traded it in FP within<BR>
the hour for 4k worth of gear and 2k cash.</font></td></tr></table>
